{"_id":"Px04LzsI56LVQ6Xv","name":"Introduction","content":"<p>@Compendium[vttoms-tower-map.journals.veFNA1GfRcKpobce]{German Introduction}</p>\n<p>This module offers a map of a tower, read to use in your game. Let your group attack or defend the tower. The different levels combined with the outside terrain give plenty of tactical challenges for an exciting battle either way.</p>\n<p>The module faces the challenge of players and NPCs on different levels of the tower acting at the same time. In order to address this challenge two separate solutions to these issues have been provided and below their respective pros and cons are laid out. Choose the one that best suits your style.</p>\n<h1>1) Scenes with Levels</h1>\n<p>Tip: Since the default height of levels does not fit The Dark Eye standard distances please deactivate the following setting.</p>\n<p><strong>Configure Settings ⇾ Module Settings ⇾  Wall Height ⇾ Automatic Token Height.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Advantages</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>All tokens are in one scene and can easily be seen.</li>\n<li>A fight takes place on a single scene, hence all combatants are in a single Combat Tracker.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Disadvantages:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>There are peculiarities in the visibility. If one token is height up at a window, another token close to the tower might not be visible. While this is realistic due to the viewing angles it can also be confusing.</li>\n<li>The module mechanics are complex. This means if you run into an issue in-depth knowledge of both Module Levels and Monk's Active Tiles are required to troubleshoot.</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>2) Scenes with Multilevel Tokens</h1>\n<p><strong>Advantages:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Multilevel Tokens only uses a single, widely used, module and therefore is easier to troubleshoot than 1) Scene with Levels.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Disadvantages:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>While you can potentially see tokens on different levels, these tokens are only clones of the original. That means they cannot be directly targetted and attacked. Any attack or action against tokens not on the same level will need to be handled manually.</li>\n<li>Combat Trackers are per scene, therefore a fight over different levels has to be processed in multiple combat trackers.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>Sidenote: Thanks to Lambert Behnke for the english translation!</em></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"AvF2Cr5deSMZuavY":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"6f945d802a2b6ffbfdcf20bb05e067ecb364aee1","sourceId":"JournalEntry.Px04LzsI56LVQ6Xv"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mh8o5uhixw","path":"Tower Map","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.vttoms-tower-map.journals.Px04LzsI56LVQ6Xv"}}}
{"_id":"QD3OLHi0ZKNVwwbQ","name":"cellar-tp","content":"<p><strong>Important! </strong></p>\n<p>This note is used for the Teleport from the well to the cellar. Because the players shouldt walk onto the well and get teleportet down, the GM should manually teleport them by setting the Token onto the teleporter and then click on this note.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Wichtig!</strong></p>\n<p>Diese Notiz dient zum Auslösen des Teleporters von Brunnen in den Keller. Damit die Spieler nicht aus versehen einfach auf den Brunnen ziehen und dann durch den Geheimgang teleportiert werden, muss der GM den Token auf den Brunnen ziehen und dann diese Notiz anklicken zum Teleportieren.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"AvF2Cr5deSMZuavY":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"fc4774d583ce9e75c727723f2c4c5c3c71eebc80","sourceId":"JournalEntry.QD3OLHi0ZKNVwwbQ"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.vttoms-tower-map.journals.QD3OLHi0ZKNVwwbQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_mh8o5uhixw","path":"Tower Map","color":"#000000"}}}
